    "narrative": "The Austin Waves face a favorable slate today, anchored by the elite 81.88 efficiency rating of **Gunnar Henderson**. Facing McCullers Jr. (4.94 xERA), **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment and a 19% boost due to the starter's lack of command. Critically for our stolen base strategy, the combination of McCullers Jr.\u2019s slow delivery and **Gunnar Henderson** leading off creates an ideal environment for him to exploit the basepaths. Joining him at the top of the projected value chart is **Jacob Wilson** (71.63), whose platoon advantage against the lefty Cameron and the premium leadoff spot make him a high-floor play despite a middling matchup.\n\nIn the middle tier, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.95) remains a cornerstone, with his high-end xwOBA and favorable SP skill matchup against Ober compensating for the minor platoon disadvantage. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.83) edges out our other options due to a strong 14% platoon boost against the right-handed Peralta, F., though the matchup remains statistically difficult. **Nasim Nunez** (45.93) is our most \"situational\" start today; while his raw offensive output is marginal, his elite sprint speed and the 4% boost derived from Peralta, F.\u2019s slow delivery make him the superior choice over bench options like **Coby Mayo** or **Brady House**, as the Waves prioritize SB efficiency in 5x5 Roto formats.\n\nRegarding our depth, **Drake Baldwin** (53.50) and **Heliot Ramos** (53.76) occupy the final active slots as reliable, albeit lower-ceiling, contributors. We are managing a significant amount of dead weight on the bench today, as **Kyle Tucker**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages** are all unavailable due to scheduling, while **Luis Robert Jr.** remains sidelined on the IL. No other players on our secondary roster, including **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Josh Jung**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Dominic Smith**, or **Liam Hicks**, presented a strong enough case to displace the current lineup given the specific platoon and velocity-based advantages we are targeting against tonight's starting pitching rotation.",
